The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 March is 41,261 (4,775.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 March, there were 271 new confirmed cases (31.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 March, there were 294 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 8% (23 fewer cases).
